data.name: txtInstructions.Text
data.value: Test Directory Tree allows you to select a top-level directory in which subfolders are assumed to represent gestures from one subject (e.g., "s01"), and subsubfolders represent gestures of a given gesture performance speed (e.g., "fast"). A single output file for the top-level directory structure is written. In reality, these two tokens (the subject name and speed name) are just used to form the first two columns of the output file, so they can be any string whatsoever.
